# GNU Stow ignore list for the `claude` package.
# A local ignore file OVERRIDES stow's built-in defaults (no merge), so the
# standard defaults are reproduced below, then `plugins/` is added.
#
# `plugins/` holds Claude Code plugin bundles that are loaded in place via
# `claude --plugin-dir $DOT_FILES/claude/plugins/<name>`. They must NOT be
# symlinked into $HOME, so stow skips the whole subtree.

# --- stow built-in defaults ---
RCS
.+,v
CVS
\.\#.+
\.cvsignore
\.svn
_darcs
\.git
\.gitignore
.+~
\#.*\#
^/README.*
^/LICENSE.*
^/COPYING

# --- this package ---
^/plugins
